1
00:00:36,039 --> 00:00:43,079
(One day before
TnT Mobile stockholders' meeting)

2
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:47,090
Dear my brother,

3
00:00:47,789 --> 00:00:51,219
I don't know how to describe
my life in the suite room here.

4
00:00:52,189 --> 00:00:55,630
Living an easeful life
must change one's face.

5
00:00:55,990 --> 00:00:58,200
My eyes shine...

6
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,570
and my skin is glossy.

7
00:01:04,900 --> 00:01:09,069
I'm doing great,
so make sure not to skip meals.

8
00:01:09,540 --> 00:01:14,180
Life in a suite room must be
beyond imagination, as I assumed.

9
00:01:26,590 --> 00:01:27,689
Who is it?

10
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:44,980
How strange. Whenever I'm back home,
there's always something...

11
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:46,480
dropped on the floor.

12
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:49,950
Could it be a thief?

13
00:01:52,049 --> 00:01:53,280
No way.

14
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:55,519
If the thief has eyes,

15
00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:57,920
he should be able to see
how miserable this place is.

16
00:02:29,389 --> 00:02:30,460
Oh, my goodness!

17
00:02:31,460 --> 00:02:33,889
I said I would swim for
just 30 minutes and go back.

18
00:02:34,490 --> 00:02:37,229
I found something amazing
and I couldn't wait.

19
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:39,930
Did you stay up all night
looking for that alone?

20
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,599
Including this,
I found five in total.

21
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,699
I'm not sure
if that's enough though.

22
00:02:47,639 --> 00:02:48,669
Let me see.

23
00:02:49,569 --> 00:02:50,639
What are you doing?

24
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:55,080
It's just that your swimming suit
looks a bit too small.

25
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:56,879
Of course swimming suits are small.

26
00:02:58,319 --> 00:03:00,490
Oh, dear. Put this on at least.

27
00:03:06,659 --> 00:03:10,060
Stay away from my son, right now!

28
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,099
Ma'am.

29
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:20,000
Your words and
this situation just now...

30
00:03:20,340 --> 00:03:22,669
can be misleading in many ways.

31
00:03:22,669 --> 00:03:24,180
Are you saying
you can't stay away from him?

32
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:28,879
What I'm going to say might sound
misleading in many ways too,

33
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:30,849
but our relationship is...

34
00:03:31,650 --> 00:03:34,550
quite serious. We can't separate
just because you tell us to.

35
00:03:34,550 --> 00:03:36,189
When you guys were seven,

36
00:03:36,620 --> 00:03:39,289
you followed Secretary Choi
and constantly came to my house.

37
00:03:39,919 --> 00:03:41,729
I should have separated
you two then already.

38
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:45,599
Then I wouldn't have had to see you
raising your hand at the meeting.

39
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:49,900
I just realized why this situation
felt familiar to me.

40
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:52,500
Something similar to this happened
when I was seven.

41
00:03:53,139 --> 00:03:55,009
That's why I'm going to
take care of it properly this time.

42
00:03:55,710 --> 00:03:57,080
If water doesn't work...

43
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:01,050
Nothing works better than this.

44
00:04:06,020 --> 00:04:08,020
This actually looks very misleading.

45
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:11,319
Think of it as severance pay
and go travel with this money.

46
00:04:11,659 --> 00:04:15,360
After this stockholders' meeting,
quit the boarder and the company.

47
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:19,600
You're shameless, but not brainless.
I'm sure you got what I mean.

48
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,829
I have to go.

49
00:04:31,310 --> 00:04:32,579
Who is it?

50
00:04:34,850 --> 00:04:36,649
Director Gi.

51
00:04:36,649 --> 00:04:37,720
Secretary Jeong.

52
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,920
What happened to your face?

53
00:04:42,089 --> 00:04:43,120
Come in.

54
00:04:50,899 --> 00:04:52,259
You haven't had coffee, have you?

55
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:55,769
The cup is supposed to be here.

56
00:04:55,769 --> 00:04:57,399
What's with this messy room?

57
00:04:57,939 --> 00:04:59,139
Are you okay?

58
00:05:04,209 --> 00:05:05,579
I would rather not drink coffee.

59
00:05:05,779 --> 00:05:06,810
Where's Min Ik?

60
00:05:08,279 --> 00:05:11,050
He's swimming now,
but he'll be back soon.

61
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,019
That...

62
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,990
Is that the list of people
who signed the power of attorney?

63
00:05:22,959 --> 00:05:24,100
Park Ok Soon.

64
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:25,600
Why hasn't she signed yet?

65
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:28,269
You said you were going to
write a power of attorney.

66
00:05:28,269 --> 00:05:29,500
I'm getting her signature today.

67
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:32,269
Really? Are you certain?

68
00:05:32,569 --> 00:05:35,339
After signing it, she's not coming
to the stockholders' meeting, right?

69
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:36,939
I guess so.

70
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:39,839
Is Park Ok Soon's signature
that important?

71
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:42,810
I remember you were checking
on that multiple times.

72
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,790
Park Ok Soon is
Veronica Park's real name.

73
00:05:52,560 --> 00:05:54,129
- Really?
- Who?

74
00:05:55,759 --> 00:05:56,759
Goodness.

75
00:05:57,199 --> 00:05:59,329
Look at you all startled.
What were you whispering about?

76
00:06:00,569 --> 00:06:01,629
Is it a secret?

77
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:03,529
Is it a scheme?

78
00:06:04,170 --> 00:06:05,240
Is it love?

79
00:06:06,069 --> 00:06:08,069
Coffee...

80
00:06:09,069 --> 00:06:13,110
Director Gi Dae Ju said
he wanted some coffee, so...

81
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:18,050
What brings you here?

82
00:06:18,550 --> 00:06:20,050
Are you here to say
you're quitting again?

83
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:22,620
I'm here to see
if you're doing all right, buster.

84
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:24,990
How have you been shoving her around
for the last two weeks?

85
00:06:24,990 --> 00:06:26,360
She looks terrible.

86
00:06:29,329 --> 00:06:30,360
What about her look?

87
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,029
Can't you see?

88
00:06:33,129 --> 00:06:35,930
Her face looks like
you put a straw on it...

89
00:06:36,069 --> 00:06:37,699
and sucked all of her soul out.

90
00:06:48,350 --> 00:06:49,480
She's imprinted on your mind.

91
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,779
Your eyes are not actually
seeing and recognizing her.

92
00:06:51,779 --> 00:06:54,689
Your brain just imprinted her
in your mind.

93
00:06:56,449 --> 00:06:58,220
Just because I can see
Secretary Jeong's face,

94
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,790
it doesn't mean
I can see her facial expressions.

95
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:04,129
Sir, why...

96
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:10,540
- Go.
- What? All of a sudden?

97
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:12,199
Did I do something wrong?

98
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:15,509
Since you've been living in such
a nice suite room until now,

99
00:07:15,970 --> 00:07:17,480
I think you can let me use it
at least for one day.

100
00:07:17,839 --> 00:07:20,279
Tomorrow's stockholders' meeting
will be held in this hotel anyway.

101
00:07:20,910 --> 00:07:24,649
I think staying here tonight will
help me stay in shape.

102
00:07:25,079 --> 00:07:26,649
You have your point, but...

103
00:07:26,649 --> 00:07:28,250
we still need to practice...

104
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:38,930
Here are the slippers, shampoos, and
conditioners you've been collecting.

105
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,370
Take them all
and go get some sleep.

106
00:07:45,439 --> 00:07:46,870
They said
those would be charged extra.

107
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:50,370
You know how embarrassing it is
if you don't use the minibar...

108
00:07:50,370 --> 00:07:51,639
in a room like this?

109
00:07:54,350 --> 00:07:57,350
I can't eat these anyway
because they have peanuts in them.

110
00:07:59,079 --> 00:08:00,149
There are no peanuts in it.

111
00:08:01,490 --> 00:08:03,860
"This product was produced
in the same factory..."

112
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,220
"that produces peanuts"!

113
00:08:10,290 --> 00:08:11,560
Take the hotel limousine.

114
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,829
- I can take the bus.
- Just take the limousine.

115
00:08:14,399 --> 00:08:16,699
Act like a guest who stayed
at a hotel suite.

116
00:08:17,339 --> 00:08:19,800
Don't walk to the bus stop
with a bag full of hotel slippers.

117
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:23,110
Call me when you get home.

118
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,540
Okay.

119
00:08:26,939 --> 00:08:28,050
Go on.

120
00:08:28,579 --> 00:08:30,250
I'll be off, then.

121
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:32,379
Will you just... Just go.

122
00:08:46,159 --> 00:08:47,200
What's wrong?

123
00:08:48,629 --> 00:08:50,129
Why don't you just drive her home?

124
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:54,340
What kind of a boss
drives his own secretary home?

125
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:08,919
"I should be sorry..."

126
00:09:09,350 --> 00:09:12,190
"to have that voice fall silent..."

127
00:09:12,519 --> 00:09:15,330
"and pass out of my life."

128
00:09:15,759 --> 00:09:16,789
Do you remember?

129
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:19,200
We wrote an essay
about this in college.

130
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,830
"The Diaries of Adam and Eve"
by Mark Twain.

131
00:09:20,830 --> 00:09:22,870
Why are you suddenly
being so poetic?

132
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:24,600
Looking at you right now...

133
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:26,700
just reminded me of that quote.

134
00:09:27,769 --> 00:09:30,039
You seem really sad...

135
00:09:31,039 --> 00:09:33,440
to see Secretary Jeong leave.

136
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:36,179
You lunatic.

137
00:09:37,519 --> 00:09:39,620
It's my camaraderie
toward my secretary...

138
00:09:39,620 --> 00:09:42,320
since she worked really hard with me
for the past two weeks.

139
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:44,190
It's my love for humanity
toward someone who's never slept...

140
00:09:44,190 --> 00:09:45,360
in a hotel suite before.

141
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:48,129
And I'm just a guy who has love
for every human being...

142
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:49,289
on earth, you jerk.

143
00:09:53,029 --> 00:09:54,100
Are you sure you're not dating her?

144
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:57,269
There's someone else I want to date.

145
00:09:57,500 --> 00:09:58,600
Really?

146
00:09:59,100 --> 00:10:00,100
Who?

147
00:10:04,340 --> 00:10:05,409
Well...

148
00:10:07,009 --> 00:10:09,610
I really didn't know I'd end up...

149
00:10:10,110 --> 00:10:12,519
liking her so much.

150
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,919
When I think of you,

151
00:10:16,049 --> 00:10:19,019
I have a funny feeling
in my stomach.

152
00:10:21,129 --> 00:10:22,889
I guess I have indigestion.

153
00:10:23,759 --> 00:10:27,000
Every time I look at her,
my heart starts racing,

154
00:10:27,700 --> 00:10:30,169
and my blood pressure goes up.

155
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:31,899
Is she pretty?

156
00:10:36,539 --> 00:10:37,539
She's pretty.

157
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:39,580
And here's what's interesting.

158
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:42,379
Her voice sounds so familiar.

159
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,580
And although it was my first time
seeing her,

160
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:49,289
it felt as though she knew me.

161
00:10:49,889 --> 00:10:51,590
You're head over heels for her.

162
00:10:51,919 --> 00:10:52,919
Hey.

163
00:10:55,690 --> 00:10:56,929
Call her.

164
00:10:57,399 --> 00:10:59,159
Let's hear her voice.

165
00:11:00,360 --> 00:11:01,669
The stockholders' meeting
is tomorrow.

166
00:11:01,669 --> 00:11:03,029
I shouldn't be thinking about her.

167
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,539
You should go.

168
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:06,940
I know you're here to tell me
that you're going to quit.

169
00:11:07,269 --> 00:11:09,370
The least you could do is call her.

170
00:11:11,980 --> 00:11:12,980
Here.

171
00:11:14,279 --> 00:11:15,710
When did I ever lend you money?

172
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:18,019
I borrowed money from your mom.

173
00:11:18,220 --> 00:11:20,620
She somehow knew I needed money
and lent me this.

174
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:24,389
Give this back to her
and thank her for me.

175
00:11:29,659 --> 00:11:31,429
And make sure to be well-prepared.

176
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:37,500
Even if I quit, you'll still be...

177
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:40,639
Here's a song by Cho PD.

178
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:43,070
"My Friend".

179
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:51,379
Hurray!

180
00:11:55,350 --> 00:11:58,289
Isn't it a great place for a date?

181
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:01,860
It's a great place
to sign a document.

182
00:12:05,159 --> 00:12:07,000
If I sign this,

183
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:10,799
what will you give me in return?

184
00:12:10,799 --> 00:12:12,600
From what I know,
you don't need anything from me...

185
00:12:12,600 --> 00:12:14,809
because you already have
everything you need.

186
00:12:14,809 --> 00:12:17,070
I may have everything I need,

187
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:20,639
but I never got anything from you.

188
00:12:21,409 --> 00:12:24,419
Then how about I treat you
to a meal?

189
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:29,090
100,000 of my shares
for just 1 meal?

190
00:12:31,059 --> 00:12:32,820
That doesn't sound too bad.

191
00:12:33,490 --> 00:12:35,730
As you already know,
I really like stuff...

192
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,960
that aren't very cost-effective.

193
00:12:44,539 --> 00:12:45,840
By the way,

194
00:12:47,240 --> 00:12:49,440
are you asking me to sign this...

195
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,139
because you're against...

196
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:54,879
the dismissal of Do Min Ik?

197
00:12:55,610 --> 00:12:57,409
Don't you trust me?

198
00:12:57,409 --> 00:12:59,980
It's because I can't trust myself.

199
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:03,419
I sometimes made the wrong choice
because of men.

200
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:06,659
And it adds up
to about 12 times in total.

201
00:13:07,059 --> 00:13:08,990
If that's what it is, don't worry.

202
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:11,299
I've never made
any bad judgements...

203
00:13:11,299 --> 00:13:12,659
because of a woman before.

204
00:13:12,860 --> 00:13:14,700
My goodness.

205
00:13:15,899 --> 00:13:21,210
I think I forgot my signature.

206
00:13:29,009 --> 00:13:30,750
There you go.

207
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:37,289
When will we get to eat together?

208
00:13:37,919 --> 00:13:40,659
I don't feel comfortable
about paying in advance.

209
00:13:46,460 --> 00:13:48,299
Please free your schedule tomorrow.

210
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:51,600
I'll treat you to a meal right after
the stockholders' meeting.

211
00:13:52,669 --> 00:13:53,669
Yes.

212
00:13:54,039 --> 00:13:56,539
I checked the file,
and everything was fine.

213
00:13:57,610 --> 00:13:59,509
No, you don't need to come.

214
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:01,509
I'll leave it where you told me to.

215
00:14:07,049 --> 00:14:08,850
(Media 2, Director Gi Dae Ju)

216
00:14:09,519 --> 00:14:10,549
I am...

217
00:14:11,860 --> 00:14:15,059
sleepy right now.

218
00:14:17,659 --> 00:14:19,029
I am...

219
00:14:20,500 --> 00:14:22,629
sleeping right now.

220
00:14:26,269 --> 00:14:28,769
I am asleep.

221
00:14:32,639 --> 00:14:35,350
I am asleep.

222
00:14:37,009 --> 00:14:40,450
Darn it! Why can't I go to sleep?

223
00:14:59,070 --> 00:15:00,139
Director Do.

224
00:15:00,899 --> 00:15:04,210
They give us two new pairs
of slippers every day.

225
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:08,480
I'm going to wear new ones
every other day,

226
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,409
so would it be okay
if I take the rest?

227
00:15:10,879 --> 00:15:11,980
Thank you.

228
00:15:33,370 --> 00:15:35,539
I spent way too much time with her.

229
00:15:49,649 --> 00:15:52,990
It's true that I love hotel buffets
more than I love myself.

230
00:15:52,990 --> 00:15:54,990
But I can't let you eat
hotel buffets...

231
00:15:54,990 --> 00:15:57,429
every single day.

232
00:15:58,029 --> 00:15:59,529
I'll cook a hearty meal for you...

233
00:15:59,529 --> 00:16:01,830
at least once a day.

234
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:05,139
At first,

235
00:16:06,370 --> 00:16:09,039
I thought she was too talkative.

236
00:16:21,419 --> 00:16:24,149
(Boss)

237
00:16:34,769 --> 00:16:36,299
Hello?

238
00:16:37,269 --> 00:16:38,299
Are you sleeping?

239
00:16:39,169 --> 00:16:40,840
Yes.

240
00:16:42,210 --> 00:16:43,509
I'm sleeping.

241
00:16:44,210 --> 00:16:45,779
You must think of me
as your friend...

242
00:16:45,779 --> 00:16:47,509
after spending
the past two weeks with me.

243
00:16:48,649 --> 00:16:51,580
Didn't I tell you to call me
once you got home?

244
00:16:52,519 --> 00:16:54,389
I'm sorry.

245
00:16:55,649 --> 00:16:58,190
I got home just fine.

246
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:00,620
Bye, then.

247
00:17:00,620 --> 00:17:03,190
I can't even sleep right now because
of the stockholders' meeting.

248
00:17:03,529 --> 00:17:05,930
But it seems like my secretary
is sleeping very well.

249
00:17:06,529 --> 00:17:08,029
What kind of attitude is that...

250
00:17:08,029 --> 00:17:09,670
when you promised to help me
become the president?

251
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:11,869
You have no respect for your boss.

252
00:17:11,869 --> 00:17:14,140
And you've forgotten your duty
as my secretary.

253
00:17:14,140 --> 00:17:16,140
Is this some sort of mutiny or what?

254
00:17:16,140 --> 00:17:17,910
"Mutiny"?

255
00:17:20,809 --> 00:17:22,750
You're the one who told me to leave.

256
00:17:22,910 --> 00:17:26,250
And is it my fault
that you can't go to sleep?

257
00:17:26,519 --> 00:17:27,519
Why don't you...

258
00:17:27,519 --> 00:17:29,789
go ahead and blame me
for your constipation?

259
00:17:29,789 --> 00:17:32,589
I don't have constipation.
You're disgusting.

260
00:17:34,019 --> 00:17:36,359
I could tell after spending
a few days with you.

261
00:17:37,359 --> 00:17:40,029
You always flush the toilet
three times.

262
00:17:40,029 --> 00:17:41,099
