the punishment I deserve.

526
00:34:32,809 --> 00:34:34,280
And it is also my duty.

527
00:34:50,389 --> 00:34:51,929
You'll save him, right?

528
00:34:55,059 --> 00:34:58,170
When my boss says he will do it,
he really does it.

529
00:34:59,099 --> 00:35:02,369
He will never waste your money.

530
00:35:03,110 --> 00:35:04,869
You can trust me.

531
00:35:04,869 --> 00:35:06,480
Since when did you like him?

532
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:08,710
Excuse me?

533
00:35:08,710 --> 00:35:11,210
You like your boss.

534
00:35:12,179 --> 00:35:14,820
What are you talking about?

535
00:35:15,380 --> 00:35:19,659
Your eyes are not saying,
"Please save my boss."

536
00:35:19,920 --> 00:35:22,530
They're saying,
"Please save my man."

537
00:35:23,329 --> 00:35:25,860
That's not what it is.

538
00:35:27,199 --> 00:35:28,800
I'm doing this purely
out of respect,

539
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,269
as I've been working with him.

540
00:35:31,730 --> 00:35:34,539
If you call that fond look
is for someone you respect,

541
00:35:34,539 --> 00:35:37,539
I'm sure you'll melt the statue
of Admiral Lee in Gwanghwamun.

542
00:35:39,280 --> 00:35:42,210
You can never tell how you look
by looking yourself in the mirror.

543
00:35:42,750 --> 00:35:44,550
You need to look from the side
to get a proper look.

544
00:35:45,179 --> 00:35:48,119
Hey, I wish I could show
your eyes just now...

545
00:35:48,119 --> 00:35:51,090
to a horrible actor.

546
00:35:51,690 --> 00:35:56,090
This is exactly what the eyes of
a person in love looks like.

547
00:35:59,199 --> 00:36:00,360
What kind of witch are you?

548
00:36:01,030 --> 00:36:03,400
It's Park Seok Ja. Your mother.

549
00:36:04,829 --> 00:36:06,539
Hello, ma'am.

550
00:36:07,039 --> 00:36:09,909
Is this a school reunion or what?
Why are you goofing around here?

551
00:36:10,239 --> 00:36:11,309
Stand up.

552
00:36:11,840 --> 00:36:15,010
I would like to say hi to
the chief director and her son.

553
00:36:15,980 --> 00:36:17,079
Let's see.

554
00:36:17,750 --> 00:36:22,289
I think I saw him somewhere here.

555
00:36:25,449 --> 00:36:26,519
Sir.

556
00:36:26,519 --> 00:36:28,119
Who was the woman next to you?

557
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:30,230
Because of that woman's question,
I...

558
00:36:30,230 --> 00:36:31,789
Get in!

559
00:36:36,269 --> 00:36:39,300
Jeong Gal Hee,
what are you doing now?

560
00:36:40,039 --> 00:36:42,070
- What are you doing?
- I know.

561
00:36:42,869 --> 00:36:44,809
What am I doing?

562
00:36:45,409 --> 00:36:47,179
You want to vote together
since we've been together...

563
00:36:48,739 --> 00:36:50,179
for the last two weeks?

564
00:36:50,179 --> 00:36:52,650
Do we really have to be
in such a small booth together?

565
00:36:53,679 --> 00:36:54,750
Let's just do it then.

566
00:36:57,650 --> 00:36:59,389
We need to go somewhere actually.

567
00:36:59,820 --> 00:37:00,889
We do?

568
00:37:06,500 --> 00:37:07,659
Okay. Let's go.

569
00:37:08,230 --> 00:37:09,230
Wait.

570
00:37:10,130 --> 00:37:11,269
(Voting Booth)

571
00:37:18,909 --> 00:37:21,780
Okay, you can go now. Right now.

572
00:37:22,809 --> 00:37:25,920
Nice to meet you.
I am Veronica Park.

573
00:37:31,489 --> 00:37:33,119
I'm sorry.

574
00:37:33,789 --> 00:37:35,059
I should've...

575
00:37:35,059 --> 00:37:37,590
taught her manners
when she was young.

576
00:37:37,789 --> 00:37:39,659
But as you already know,

577
00:37:39,659 --> 00:37:42,469
I had to work really hard
for TnT Mobile,

578
00:37:42,469 --> 00:37:44,170
so I didn't have much time...

579
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:46,039
to be around her back then.

580
00:37:47,699 --> 00:37:51,070
Your daughter managed
to turn that Seokja Corporation...

581
00:37:51,340 --> 00:37:54,340
into our country's
top culture company.

582
00:37:57,650 --> 00:37:59,920
Nice to meet you. I'm Sim Hae Ra.

583
00:38:02,289 --> 00:38:05,349
I heard things are going well
with my son.

584
00:38:06,619 --> 00:38:07,690
Me?

585
00:38:10,059 --> 00:38:13,730
So you told them I was there?

586
00:38:13,929 --> 00:38:15,000
Yes.

587
00:38:15,300 --> 00:38:18,699
I told them
you actually met each other.

588
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:23,170
Yes, that's right.

589
00:38:23,909 --> 00:38:27,239
This brat rarely attends
stockholders' meetings.

590
00:38:27,539 --> 00:38:30,880
But she purposely came today
to meet your son.

591
00:38:30,980 --> 00:38:33,650
My goodness, is that so?

592
00:38:34,949 --> 00:38:36,550
Then you should say hello.

593
00:38:37,119 --> 00:38:38,489
Where did he go?

594
00:38:42,289 --> 00:38:43,659
Where are we going?

595
00:38:46,599 --> 00:38:48,260
- Give me your cell phone.
- What?

596
00:38:48,260 --> 00:38:49,670
Give me your cell phone.

597
00:38:52,969 --> 00:38:54,269
Director Do.

598
00:39:02,710 --> 00:39:03,750
Get in.

599
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:05,849
Where are we going?

600
00:39:05,849 --> 00:39:07,250
It's working hours right now.

601
00:39:07,250 --> 00:39:09,389
Are you refusing to follow
your boss' orders?

602
00:39:10,690 --> 00:39:11,719
Get in.

603
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:18,090
How are the stockholders?

604
00:39:18,659 --> 00:39:19,730
Will things go as planned?

605
00:39:19,730 --> 00:39:22,829
It seems like a few of them
got swayed.

606
00:39:22,829 --> 00:39:25,099
But small investors can't make
that much of a difference.

607
00:39:25,429 --> 00:39:28,539
The major stockholders already
made up their minds coming here.

608
00:39:28,539 --> 00:39:30,940
It's all about
how many votes we get,

609
00:39:30,940 --> 00:39:32,309
so don't worry too much.

610
00:39:33,340 --> 00:39:35,849
The problem is...

611
00:39:35,849 --> 00:39:38,909
that we don't know
what she's going to vote for.

612
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,050
Let me get this straight.

613
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:44,949
If I vote for you...

614
00:39:44,949 --> 00:39:47,619
at your company's
stockholders' meeting,

615
00:39:47,889 --> 00:39:49,960
you're going to vote for me...

616
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:52,360
at our company's
stockholders' meeting?

617
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:55,130
Are you suggesting that we should
mutually help each other?

618
00:39:55,130 --> 00:39:56,500
It's more like repaying my thanks.

619
00:39:56,500 --> 00:39:57,800
It's only right...

620
00:39:57,800 --> 00:40:00,639
for me to repay my thanks
to someone I'm indebted to.

621
00:40:01,269 --> 00:40:02,340
Do you know that I purchased...

622
00:40:02,340 --> 00:40:04,969
an additional 80,000
of Cinepark's shares?

623
00:40:09,750 --> 00:40:10,750
President Park.

624
00:40:11,610 --> 00:40:13,920
Goodness, President Sim.

625
00:40:14,019 --> 00:40:16,019
You should make a wise choice.

626
00:40:16,789 --> 00:40:19,789
You don't want to lose money
by getting swayed.

627
00:40:19,789 --> 00:40:21,119
Of course.

628
00:40:21,559 --> 00:40:25,130
I can't let myself make
another wrong judgement...

629
00:40:25,130 --> 00:40:28,030
because of a guy.

630
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:42,809
Your destination is 2km away.

631
00:40:43,650 --> 00:40:45,550
Where are we going?

632
00:40:47,619 --> 00:40:50,019
Then can I at least have
my cell phone back?

633
00:40:50,019 --> 00:40:51,820
What are you doing?
Get your hands off me.

634
00:40:52,250 --> 00:40:53,760
You're not kidnapping me, are you?

635
00:40:53,960 --> 00:40:57,059
Wasn't it your wish to have grilled
clams with a bottle of soju...

636
00:40:57,260 --> 00:40:59,559
after the stockholders' meeting?

637
00:41:01,500 --> 00:41:04,030
Director Do,
it's true that I felt...

638
00:41:04,030 --> 00:41:06,440
extremely nervous and anxious
to attend...

639
00:41:06,440 --> 00:41:08,400
the stockholders' meeting.
But still...

640
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:11,409
I don't think we should be gone
when it isn't even over.

641
00:41:11,510 --> 00:41:12,510
Turn back the car.

642
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:15,139
Will you be able to relax
if I tell you this?

643
00:41:15,639 --> 00:41:19,150
What if there's another good reason
why we should celebrate...

644
00:41:19,420 --> 00:41:20,480
apart from
the stockholders' meeting?

645
00:41:21,679 --> 00:41:22,820
What's that?

646
00:41:31,030 --> 00:41:32,090
I can see.

647
00:41:43,309 --> 00:41:45,440
(TnT Mobile
Extraordinary Stockholders' Meeting)

648
00:41:50,610 --> 00:41:52,980
I'll announce the results.

649
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:59,420
A total of 125,116,807 shares
participated in the vote.

650
00:41:59,420 --> 00:42:03,030
And the number of shares that voted
for the agenda is five thousand...

651
00:42:15,039 --> 00:42:16,070
Here.

652
00:42:16,710 --> 00:42:18,239
You want me to grill them?

653
00:42:18,239 --> 00:42:19,940
Of course.
Do you expect me to grill them?

654
00:42:19,940 --> 00:42:22,139
I kindly drove you all the way here.

655
00:42:22,610 --> 00:42:24,280
Shouldn't you be grateful?

656
00:42:25,210 --> 00:42:27,449
It seems like you got
the wrong idea.

657
00:42:27,449 --> 00:42:30,050
When I said I wanted to eat
grilled clams,

658
00:42:30,050 --> 00:42:31,690
I meant that I wanted to eat it
with someone I like,

659
00:42:31,690 --> 00:42:34,190
hearing sounds
of the waves in the background.

660
00:42:34,389 --> 00:42:35,789
I didn't mean
I wanted to put on work gloves...

661
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:38,760
and grill clams for my boss
like a minion.

662
00:42:42,929 --> 00:42:46,400
Here. Will this make you happy?

663
00:42:57,610 --> 00:42:59,579
About that USB I told you about...

664
00:42:59,579 --> 00:43:02,219
I looked for it everywhere,
but I couldn't find it.

665
00:43:02,750 --> 00:43:04,119
- You couldn't find it?
- No.

666
00:43:04,449 --> 00:43:06,920
I'm sure I put it in my drawer,
but it was gone.

667
00:43:07,289 --> 00:43:10,230
But thankfully, I copied the files
onto my laptop.

668
00:43:10,230 --> 00:43:13,730
It was in the suit you wore
on the day of the accident.

669
00:43:13,730 --> 00:43:15,659
So I got worried
that it might not work.

670
00:43:24,710 --> 00:43:26,809
The results should be out by now.

671
00:43:33,949 --> 00:43:35,880
If you won the vote,
it'll be a celebratory drink.

672
00:43:36,519 --> 00:43:39,519
If not,
it'll be a drink of consolation.

673
00:43:44,460 --> 00:43:48,000
I hereby announce that
Director Do Min Ik's dismissal...

674
00:43:48,400 --> 00:43:50,730
(For: 50,005,500,
Against: 55,111,307)

675
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:00,139
(Mister Grilled Clams)

676
00:44:00,139 --> 00:44:01,510
What are you thinking?

677
00:44:02,750 --> 00:44:05,849
I'm surprised that a human's mind
can be so complicated...

678
00:44:06,650 --> 00:44:09,150
even when looking at
a very calming scenery.

679
00:44:09,690 --> 00:44:10,889
What about you?

680
00:44:13,019 --> 00:44:14,960
I'm just glad
that I came here with you.

681
00:44:23,170 --> 00:44:25,730
Grilled clams taste best when
my secretary grills them for me.

682
00:44:31,210 --> 00:44:33,840
They look so happy.

683
00:44:34,309 --> 00:44:35,710
Aren't they fighting?

684
00:44:35,710 --> 00:44:37,050
They're in love.

685
00:44:37,050 --> 00:44:38,610
I can tell just by
looking at her face.

686
00:44:43,820 --> 00:44:46,889
You can never tell how you look
by looking yourself in the mirror.

687
00:44:47,690 --> 00:44:49,360
You need to look from the side
to get a proper look.

688
00:44:51,030 --> 00:44:52,059
She's right.

689
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:57,630
I can see properly from the side.

690
00:44:59,699 --> 00:45:00,699
See what?

691
00:45:02,340 --> 00:45:03,340
It's nothing.

692
00:45:03,340 --> 00:45:07,079
What were you
going to tell me earlier?

693
00:45:07,079 --> 00:45:08,610
You said there's
another good reason...

694
00:45:08,610 --> 00:45:11,210
why we should celebrate apart from
the stockholders' meeting.

695
00:45:14,949 --> 00:45:16,019
Well...

696
00:45:16,719 --> 00:45:20,059
It happened only for a short moment
when I was on stage.

697
00:45:21,260 --> 00:45:22,460
Just a second.

698
00:45:22,829 --> 00:45:24,090
(Gi Dae Ju)

699
00:45:26,730 --> 00:45:28,000
The results must be out.

700
00:45:29,030 --> 00:45:30,070
You should answer it.

701
00:45:31,599 --> 00:45:33,269
Answer the phone.

702
00:45:38,610 --> 00:45:39,780
Where are you?

703
00:45:40,039 --> 00:45:41,039
Hey.

704
00:45:42,010 --> 00:45:43,079
Okay.

705
00:45:44,150 --> 00:45:45,309
Okay, bye.

706
00:45:52,050 --> 00:45:53,119
What did he say?

707
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:54,789
Secretary Jeong.

708
00:45:56,260 --> 00:45:59,860
Do you think that bird over there
is a seagull or a wild goose?

709
00:46:00,030 --> 00:46:01,929
My gosh. Come on, Director Do.

710
00:46:02,699 --> 00:46:03,699
What did he say?

711
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:06,340
The drink we had earlier...

712
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:08,469
Was it a celebratory drink?

713
00:46:09,769 --> 00:46:11,539
Or was it a drink of consolation?

714
00:46:20,349 --> 00:46:21,349
A celebratory drink.

715
00:46:24,989 --> 00:46:26,019
A celebratory drink?

716
00:46:27,059 --> 00:46:29,289
Director Do, congratulations.

717
00:46:29,489 --> 00:46:30,889
Congratulations.

718
00:47:18,170 --> 00:47:20,880
Great job, Secretary Jeong.

719
00:47:42,230 --> 00:47:43,500
I got you a gift.

720
00:47:45,230 --> 00:47:47,269
I was going to give you
before the announcement.

721
00:47:49,610 --> 00:47:50,670
Here.

722
00:47:53,409 --> 00:47:54,610
Open the trunk.

723
00:47:54,840 --> 00:47:55,840
The trunk?

724
00:47:57,250 --> 00:47:59,010
Why did you keep
the gift in the trunk?

725
00:48:04,889 --> 00:48:09,789
(Mister Grilled Clams)

726
00:48:09,789 --> 00:48:11,230
Gosh.

727
00:48:12,030 --> 00:48:15,829
Are there thousands of roses
and millions of balloons?

728
00:48:16,869 --> 00:48:19,599
I don't like surprises like that.

729
00:48:25,039 --> 00:48:27,179
What? There's nothing in there.

730
00:48:27,880 --> 00:48:29,980
There's something. Look carefully.

731
00:48:31,610 --> 00:48:33,250
What's in there?

732
00:48:39,090 --> 00:48:40,090
Is this it?

733
00:48:48,900 --> 00:48:49,900
(TnT Mobile
Extraordinary Stockholders' Meeting)

734
00:48:49,900 --> 00:48:51,530
Min Ik stays in office?

735
00:48:56,199 --> 00:48:57,539
Well done, Min Ik.

736
00:49:01,639 --> 00:49:02,639
(President Sim Hae Yong)

737
00:49:12,989 --> 00:49:14,159
Mr. Gi Dae Ju?

738
00:49:14,820 --> 00:49:17,429
Where are we having dinner tonight?

739
00:49:17,730 --> 00:49:21,030
I think I deserve something
in return of my 100,000 shares.

740
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:23,829
- I'm sorry, but...
- But?

741
00:49:28,099 --> 00:49:29,469
Did I tell you this?

742
00:49:30,570 --> 00:49:31,840
I'm a jerk...

743
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:34,780
worse than you think.

744
00:49:38,409 --> 00:49:41,420
I'm sorry, but I can't
have dinner with you today.

745
00:49:49,460 --> 00:49:50,989
He's so attractive.

746
00:50:02,739 --> 00:50:04,869
I'm really nervous here.

747
00:50:04,869 --> 00:50:07,210
Can I just open this here?

748
00:50:07,940 --> 00:50:10,449
I told you to open it
when you get home.

749
00:50:11,250 --> 00:50:13,380
I'm so curious that I can't help it.

750
00:50:13,480 --> 00:50:14,750
How much would it be?

751
00:50:15,380 --> 00:50:16,389
How much?

752
00:50:17,250 --> 00:50:19,150
Isn't this money? A monetary gift.

753
00:50:21,360 --> 00:50:24,190
In the world you live in,
is money the only thing...

754
00:50:24,559 --> 00:50:25,929
that can be in an envelope?

755
00:50:26,599 --> 00:50:28,630
Can't you expand your mind
and think further?

756
00:50:31,199 --> 00:50:32,429
No way.

757
00:50:33,840 --> 00:50:35,000
Is this a hand-written letter?

758
00:50:37,440 --> 00:50:39,440
It's just useless.

759
00:50:40,880 --> 00:50:44,710
If you have anything to say,
you can just text me.

760
00:50:46,280 --> 00:50:48,449
Gosh, just open it.

761
00:50:49,820 --> 00:50:50,849
Gosh.

762
00:50:58,690 --> 00:50:59,929
A contract?

763
00:51:03,699 --> 00:51:06,570
I'm going to say this only once,
so listen carefully.

764
00:51:07,599 --> 00:51:09,070
I had a secretary.

765
00:51:10,039 --> 00:51:11,039
Three years ago.

766
00:51:13,579 --> 00:51:17,079
But the secretary whom I
trusted and followed the most...

767
00:51:18,079 --> 00:51:19,750
deceived and betrayed me...

768
00:51:20,820 --> 00:51:23,489
at the most critical moment.

769
00:51:25,719 --> 00:51:27,920
Since then, I worked my fingers
to the bone.

770
00:51:28,719 --> 00:51:29,719
And I decided...

771
00:51:30,789 --> 00:51:32,260
not to trust secretaries anymore.

772
00:51:35,429 --> 00:51:36,630
I know...

773
00:51:37,869 --> 00:51:40,440
I fired you, hated you,

774
00:51:41,369 --> 00:51:42,969
bullied you,
and gave you a hard time.

775
00:51:44,670 --> 00:51:46,309
But it's not that I hated you.

776
00:51:48,480 --> 00:51:49,849
I hated that old secretary.

777
00:51:53,110 --> 00:51:54,719
It's her who deceived me.

778
00:51:56,179 --> 00:51:57,949
It's not like you did it to me.

779
00:52:02,159 --> 00:52:03,289
But I was afraid...

780
00:52:05,260 --> 00:52:06,699
you'd be just like her.

781
00:52:08,630 --> 00:52:10,900
It was me being in fear.

782
00:52:13,340 --> 00:52:17,110
If I've upset you,
please understand me.

783
00:52:19,369 --> 00:52:22,280
And if you're interested,

784
00:52:24,179 --> 00:52:25,679
I want you to sign a new contract.

785
00:52:28,349 --> 00:52:29,519
You know what?

786
00:52:30,619 --> 00:52:32,550
I'm deceiving you too.

787
00:52:34,619 --> 00:52:36,730
As you'll see...

788
00:52:37,789 --> 00:52:40,559
"As soon as my disease is cured,
the contract between you and me..."

789
00:52:41,030 --> 00:52:42,559
"will be terminated."

790
00:52:43,059 --> 00:52:47,900
I changed that article
into something more beautiful.

791
00:52:50,309 --> 00:52:52,840
(Article 1, Term of Contract,
It ends when the secretary asks.)

792
00:52:53,340 --> 00:52:56,110
"The contract ends..."

793
00:52:56,909 --> 00:52:58,949
"when the secretary asks"?

794
00:53:04,019 --> 00:53:05,190
Director Do.

795
00:53:05,320 --> 00:53:09,059
What do you think? Your heart
is fluttering with joy, right?

796
00:53:11,630 --> 00:53:15,530
Why? That's the only thing
you wanted from me.

797
00:53:16,099 --> 00:53:17,969
Stable employment.

798
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:21,739
I don't have to
see it to believe it.

799
00:53:22,099 --> 00:53:24,070
I know what's the look on your face.

800
00:53:26,780 --> 00:53:29,010
For your boss
who can't read your face,

801
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:33,420
tell me about the look
on your face right now...

802
00:53:33,420 --> 00:53:34,750
in detail.

803
00:53:35,820 --> 00:53:36,889
Well...

804
00:53:39,849 --> 00:53:40,920
I'm...

805
00:53:44,260 --> 00:53:45,489
I'm smiling.

806
00:53:46,900 --> 00:53:49,800
I'm smiling brightly
from ear to ear.

807
00:53:54,869 --> 00:53:57,139
My cheeks are on their way up.

808
00:54:00,539 --> 00:54:02,440
The middle of
my forehead is so flat.

809
00:54:05,750 --> 00:54:09,619
And I got wrinkles around my eyes.

810
00:54:10,650 --> 00:54:11,989
Because I'm smiling too much.

811
00:54:22,559 --> 00:54:23,670
If...

812
00:54:25,300 --> 00:54:26,469
What if...

813
00:54:30,210 --> 00:54:33,170
I'm deceiving you too?

814
00:54:35,239 --> 00:54:36,309
What?

815
00:54:36,849 --> 00:54:37,949
What if...

816
00:54:39,050 --> 00:54:42,280
there's something
I've been lying about?

817
00:54:53,230 --> 00:54:54,429
Then...

818
00:54:56,929 --> 00:54:57,929
I won't be able...

819
00:55:00,769 --> 00:55:02,440
to trust people
for the rest of my life.

820
00:55:07,409 --> 00:55:08,539
Wait.

821
00:55:10,309 --> 00:55:11,409
Hello?

822
00:55:12,179 --> 00:55:14,420
Well done. Where are you?

823
00:55:15,079 --> 00:55:16,789
I'm outside now.

824
00:55:17,090 --> 00:55:20,519
We're going out to have dinner.
You should come.

825
00:55:20,920 --> 00:55:22,489
We? Who?

826
00:55:22,719 --> 00:55:24,190
Did you not see her?

827
00:55:25,860 --> 00:55:28,199
Veronica says she came here
to see you today.

828
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:31,730
Veronica came to see me?

829
00:55:33,170 --> 00:55:35,340
Yes. Okay. Bye.

830
00:55:37,010 --> 00:55:38,110
What do I do?

831
00:55:40,380 --> 00:55:41,780
Will you go?

832
00:55:41,780 --> 00:55:44,449
How long does it take
to drive to Seoul?

833
00:55:44,579 --> 00:55:45,650
Is the traffic bad?

834
00:55:49,150 --> 00:55:50,420
Don't go.

835
00:55:52,190 --> 00:55:53,250
What?

836
00:55:54,190 --> 00:55:55,690
Please don't go.

837
00:55:56,590 --> 00:55:57,630
Why not?

838
00:56:00,400 --> 00:56:04,329
I'm not sure where I should begin
and how to explain it.

839
00:56:04,469 --> 00:56:06,769
Whether it's an excuse or
explanation, we can do that later.

840
00:56:06,940 --> 00:56:10,269
Shall we go to Seoul now?

841
00:56:13,039 --> 00:56:15,340
Do you want to see her that bad?

842
00:56:15,510 --> 00:56:16,679
Did you not hear me?

843
00:56:17,050 --> 00:56:19,480
Veronica Park came to see me.

844
00:56:21,920 --> 00:56:24,789
I want to go. I want to meet her.

845
00:56:33,530 --> 00:56:34,599
Okay.

846
00:56:36,099 --> 00:56:37,130
Go.

847
00:56:38,530 --> 00:56:41,570
Before I explain, it'd be better...

848
00:56:43,340 --> 00:56:45,639
for you to see it yourself.

849
00:56:47,239 --> 00:56:48,309
Right.

850
00:57:02,389 --> 00:57:03,489
Hurry up.

851
00:57:18,639 --> 00:57:20,639
Why? Aren't you getting in?

852
00:57:22,110 --> 00:57:23,650
I'm not going.

853
00:57:24,150 --> 00:57:25,179
What?

854
00:57:26,980 --> 00:57:28,619
I need to sober up.

855
00:57:28,619 --> 00:57:30,050
You go first.

856
00:57:36,829 --> 00:57:38,289
The sun will go down soon.

857
00:57:39,030 --> 00:57:40,429
How are you going to
go home by yourself?

858
00:57:42,329 --> 00:57:44,900
I put water on the passenger seat,

859
00:57:44,900 --> 00:57:46,840
so drink it when you get thirsty.

860
00:57:48,139 --> 00:57:49,900
You almost ran out of gas,

861
00:57:50,309 --> 00:57:52,769
so make sure to fill up the tank
before entering the highway.

862
00:57:53,469 --> 00:57:56,280
Don't drive too fast
because you feel rushed.

863
00:57:56,949 --> 00:57:57,980
And...

864
00:58:01,949 --> 00:58:03,019
Well...

865
00:58:04,690 --> 00:58:08,960
While talking to Veronica Park,

866
00:58:10,789 --> 00:58:14,099
you will want to
hear something from me.

867
00:58:15,929 --> 00:58:18,530
Then feel free to call me.

868
00:58:20,769 --> 00:58:22,340
I will tell you everything.

869
00:58:23,340 --> 00:58:25,510
Do you know you're acting
really weird now?

870
00:58:27,739 --> 00:58:30,139
Didn't you say you can
easily drink a bottle of soju?

871
00:58:33,849 --> 00:58:36,420
Go before the traffic gets worse.

872
00:59:40,079 --> 00:59:42,980
(The Secret Life of My Secretary)

873
00:59:43,179 --> 00:59:45,690
Are you going to meet Veronica Park?

874
00:59:45,719 --> 00:59:46,750
Let's break up.

875
00:59:46,750 --> 00:59:48,789
The relationship
between your boss and me.

876
00:59:49,519 --> 00:59:52,329
You don't want to
make contracts with me anymore?

877
00:59:52,329 --> 00:59:53,630
- Is that what you're saying?
- Yes.

878
00:59:53,630 --> 00:59:54,630
"Yes"? Gosh!

879
00:59:55,659 --> 00:59:56,800
Secretary Jeong.

880
00:59:57,130 --> 01:00:00,900
Can you stay by my side?
